    "sections": [
        {
            "heading": "MQTT (Telemetry) Security",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Discovery & Anonymous Access",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Scan for MQTT brokers (1883/8883)",
                        "nmap -p 1883,8883 --script mqtt-subscribe target.com",
                        "",
                        "# Check for anonymous access using mosquitto_sub",
                        "mosquitto_sub -h target.com -t '#' -v",
                        "",
                        "# Shodan query for open brokers",
                        "shodan search \"port:1883 mqtt\""
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Enumeration & Topic Infiltration",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Subscribe to all topics (wildcard)",
                        "mosquitto_sub -h target.com -t '#' -v",
                        "",
                        "# Monitor specific status levels",
                        "mosquitto_sub -h target.com -t '+/+/status' -v",
                        "",
                        "# Enumerate system topics via $SYS",
                        "mosquitto_sub -h target.com -t '$SYS/#' -v"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Active Exploitation Tools",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "[MQTT Explorer](https://mqtt-explorer.com/) - High-density GUI for topic visualization.",
                        "[mqtt-pwn](https://github.com/akamai-threat-research/mqtt-pwn) - Comprehensive MQTT reconnaissance and exploitation framework.",
                        "[mosquitto_pub](https://mosquitto.org/) - CLI for message injection and flood-based DoS."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "CoAP & Zigbee Security",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "CoAP Discovery & Amplification",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Discover resources on constrained devices",
                        "coap-client -m get coap://target.com/.well-known/core",
                        "",
                        "# Retrieve specific sensor data",
                        "coap-client -m get coap://target.com/sensors/temp",
                        "",
                        "# Resource modification (PUT)",
                        "coap-client -m put coap://target.com/actuators/switch -e \"on\""
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Zigbee Sniffing & Key Extraction",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Network discovery with KillerBee",
                        "killerbee zbstumbler",
                        "",
                        "# Capture Zigbee traffic to PCAP",
                        "killerbee zbdump -c 11 -w capture.pcap",
                        "",
                        "# Inject packets using zbinject",
                        "zbinject -c 11 -p [packet_data]"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Zigbee Hardware & Security Issues",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "**Hardware**: CC2531 USB dongle, HackRF One, and YARD Stick One.",
                        "**Vulnerabilities**: Default Trust Center Link Keys, insecure rejoin processes, and lack of replay protection.",
                        "**KillerBee**: The industry-standard framework for Zigbee protocol manipulation."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "BLE & Z-Wave Analysis",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "BLE Service Enumeration",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Scan for BLE devices",
                        "bettercap -eval \"ble.recon on\"",
                        "",
                        "# Connect and enumerate GATT services",
                        "gatttool -b AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF -I",
                        "[AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF][LE]> connect",
                        "[AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF][LE]> primary",
                        "[AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF][LE]> characteristics"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Z-Wave S0 Key Extraction",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "**Key Exchange Flaw**: S0 security features a known flaw where the network key is XORed with a constant during inclusion.",
                        "**Tools**: [EZ-Wave](https://github.com/cureHsu/EZ-Wave) for interface manipulation and packet injection.",
                        "**Hardware**: Z-Wave.Me UZB stick or specialized HackRF configurations."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "LoRaWAN & Low-Level Hardware",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "LoRaWAN Attack Vectors",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "**Replay Attacks**: Join-request replay and ACK spoofing in the absence of frame counters.",
                        "**Bit-Flipping**: Manipulating traffic data when integrity checks are misconfigured.",
                        "**Traffic Analysis**: Using [gr-lora](https://github.com/rpp0/gr-lora) for signal processing and decryption."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "General IoT Firmware Analysis",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Extract filesystem from firmware blob",
                        "binwalk -e firmware.bin",
                        "",
                        "# Modify and repack firmware",
                        "firmware-mod-kit (fmk)",
                        "",
                        "# Protocol analysis with Scapy",
                        "scapy  # Custom parsing for proprietary protocols"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
